      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When the minimum wage increases in a state, it may negatively impact small businesses like yours in rural areas. This is because rural businesses often operate on tighter profit margins, making it more challenging to absorb cost increases without passing them on to customers in the form of higher prices. Additionally, the lower cost of living and reduced tax base in rural areas may make it more difficult for businesses to justify the increased costs associated with the higher wage.",
      "source": "target",
