      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "There's no clear consensus on the exact impact of minimum wage hikes on small businesses, and various studies have yielded mixed results. While some research suggests that higher minimum wages can lead to slower job growth and reduced hiring, especially for small businesses, others argue that increased worker spending power can boost local economies. A more accurate assessment might be that the effect of higher minimum wages on small businesses depends on factors like business model, size, location, and industry.",
      "source": "target",
